# Backend Conventions

## Structure

- `app/models/` — SQLAlchemy models (snake_case columns)
- `app/schemas/` — Pydantic request/response (camelCase API aliases)
- `app/api/` — Route handlers (thin)
- `app/services/` — Business logic (status machine, CSV export)

## Acting User

- Dependency: resolve `X-User-Id` header to User; reject missing/invalid
- Set `createdBy` from acting user on ticket/comment create

## Validation

- Use Pydantic for request bodies
- Return consistent error shape: `detail`, `code`, optional `fields`
- Status changes only via dedicated status endpoint + state machine service

## Database

- Alembic for all schema changes
- Do not edit applied migrations

## Tests

- Pytest with FastAPI TestClient
- Integration tests for status transitions in `tests/integration/`
